reviewText: The DVD From Hell to Texas is a resurrection of another Don Murray movie (Bus Stop - M Monroe, These Thousand Hills). If you like Westerns you will like this one, and it includes reflections of what makes people good - and what makes them bad.  Strong cast, sets, scoring, and loaded with Western flavor and Winchester gunman-ship.  Thanks to Henry Hathaway, this movie shares locations (Lone Tree, California) with True Grit (J Wayne), North to Alaska, and Shoot Out (G Peck). The movie is five stars plus, but Warner Bros gets one star for releasing it in "little box."  Most of us didn't get large digital televisions to watch a little box a fraction the size of the screen.
Title: From Hell To Texas

reviewText: Veteran director Henry Hathaway's seldom seen western with Don Murray, Chill Wills and Diana Varsi is an off-beat but thoroughly enjoyable treat.  Don't miss it.
Title: From Hell To Texas

reviewText: This is a good standard western, one of the few films Don Murray made for Fox.  This release is in Cinsmascope 2.35 ratio and not pan and scan as indicated on this site. Good transfer from Fox Archive - and not 1.33.
summary: good Cinemascope western from Fox Archive
Title: From Hell To Texas
